    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1915-03-11T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1915-03-11T00:00:00-05:00" n="846"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d846">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 812.00/14552.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                            <gloss type="to">Spanish Ambassador</gloss>.</hi>
                    <note n="15" xml:id="d846fn15">The same to the Ambassadors of Russia, France,
                        Germany and Great Britain.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1915-03-11">
                            <hi rend="italic">March 11, 1915</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">My dear Mr. Ambassador</hi>: I enclose herewith, for your
                    information, a copy of a telegram<note n="16" xml:id="d846fn16">Of March 10, 4
                        p.m.</note> from Mr. John R. Silliman, the Department’s special
                    representative at Vera Cruz, Mexico, in regard to an intimation given by General
                    Venustiano Carranza that he does not understand the Department’s position in
                    making representations in behalf of other nationals who have their own
                    representatives at Vera Cruz.</p>
                <p>I am [etc.]</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">W. J. Bryan.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
